],"tags":[14,114,298,206,205,22,31],"class_list":["post-4954","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-quran-exegesis-tafsir","tag-good-character-husn-khuluq","tag-manners-adab","tag-muhammad","tag-prophetic-biography-seerah-nabawiyya","tag-prophetic-virtues-manaqib-nabawi","tag-al-quran","tag-virtue-al-fadail"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-1hU","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":28975,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/muhammad-no-better-akhlaq-adab\/","url_meta":{"origin":4954,"position":0},"title":"Aisha on Muhammad: None had better character than the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Urwah reported: Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, said, \u201cNo one had better character than the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him. No one from his companions or his family called upon him but that he would say: I am at your service. For this reason,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":10425,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/12\/17\/muhammad-three-things-liar\/","url_meta":{"origin":4954,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Muhammad: Whoever says this about the Prophet is a liar","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Masruq reported: I asked Aisha, \u201cO mother, did Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him, see his Lord?\u201d Aisha said, \u201cWhat you said makes my hair stand on end! Know that if someone tells you one of three things, he is a liar. Whoever tells you that Muhammad saw his\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7683,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/05\/prophet-wife-mood-aisha\/","url_meta":{"origin":4954,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Marriage: The Prophet can recognize his wife&#8217;s mood","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIndeed, I can tell when you are angry or pleased with me.\u201d I said, \u201cHow do you know that, O Messenger of Allah?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, when you are pleased, you say: Yes, by the Lord\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7669,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/05\/best-speech-kitab-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":4954,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hidayah: Best speech is Quran, best guide is Muhammad","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Tariq reported: Abdullah ibn Mas'ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, the best speech is the book of Allah, and the best guidance is the guidance of Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6098 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0637\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u0642\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0634\u0650\u0647\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17034,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/11\/25\/reminded-me-of-ayat\/","url_meta":{"origin":4954,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Allah have mercy on one who reminded me","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 25, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was listening to a man recite the Quran in the mosque and he said, \u201cMay Allah have mercy upon him. He reminded me of a verse I was made to forget.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5038, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 788 Grade: Muttafaqun\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6770,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/21\/prophet-describes-wahy\/","url_meta":{"origin":4954,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Wahy: The Prophet describes his revelations","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 21, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Al-Harith ibn Hisham asked, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how do you receive revelation?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cSometimes it is revealed like the ringing of a bell. This form of revelation is the hardest of all, but this hardship subsides once\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u